    • Method Detail

      • setFolder

        public VirtualMachinesTypes.RestorePlacementSpec.Builder setFolder(java.lang.String folder)
        Virtual machine folder into which the restored virtual machine should be placed. If property is null, the system will use the default virtual machine folder of the datacenter. If this results in a conflict due to other placement parameters, the virtual machine restore operation will fail.
        Parameters:
        folder - New value for the property. When clients pass a value of this class as a parameter, the property must be an identifier for the resource type: Folder. When methods return a value of this class as a return value, the property will be an identifier for the resource type: Folder.

      • setResourcePool

        public VirtualMachinesTypes.RestorePlacementSpec.Builder setResourcePool(java.lang.String resourcePool)
        Resource pool into which the restored virtual machine should be placed. If property is null, the system will use the other placement parameters to create virtual machine. If this results in a conflict due to other placement parameters, the virtual machine restore operation will fail.
        Parameters:
        resourcePool - New value for the property. When clients pass a value of this class as a parameter, the property must be an identifier for the resource type: ResourcePool. When methods return a value of this class as a return value, the property will be an identifier for the resource type: ResourcePool.

      • setHost

        public VirtualMachinesTypes.RestorePlacementSpec.Builder setHost(java.lang.String host)
        Host onto which the restored virtual machine should be placed.

        If getHost() and getResourcePool() are both specified, getResourcePool() must belong to getHost().

        If getHost() is specified, getHost() must be a member of cluster.

        If this property is unset, if getResourcePool() is set, and the target is a DRS cluster, a host will be picked by DRS. if getResourcePool() is unset, and the target is a DRS cluster, a host will be picked by DRS. if getResourcePool() is set, and the target is a cluster without DRS, InvalidArgument will be thrown.
        Parameters:
        host - New value for the property. When clients pass a value of this class as a parameter, the property must be an identifier for the resource type: HostSystem. When methods return a value of this class as a return value, the property will be an identifier for the resource type: HostSystem.
